<p>I am attempting to call a rather large web service.  I used <code>svcutil.exe</code> to generate classes from the wsdl and xsd for the service and get about 29,000 lines of C#.  I'd like to make the result look as close to their samples as possible.  Is there a way to change the serialization to include namespaces in a certain way?  For instance, this is what I see in Fiddler when I call the service:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;searchRequest xmlns="urn:siemens:names:prov:gw:SPML:2:0"&gt;   &lt;base xmlns=""&gt;     &lt;objectclass&gt;Car&lt;/objectclass&gt;     &lt;alias name="color" value="blue"/&gt;   &lt;/base&gt; &lt;/searchRequest&gt; </code></pre>  <p>What they have in their samples is like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;spml:searchRequest   xmlns:spml="urn:siemens:names:prov:gw:SPML:2:0"&gt;   &lt;base&gt;     &lt;objectclass&gt;Car&lt;objectclass&gt;     &lt;alias name="color" value="blue"/&gt;   &lt;/base&gt; &lt;/spml:searchRequest&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I think I need to have the namespace named and display it on the searchRequest element.  That should keep out the reset to a blank namespace on the base element.  I think I can control that on properties of the class using <code>XmlElementAttribute(Form=XmlSchemaForm.Qualified)</code>, but the searchRequest is a parameter on the web service call and I don't know how to control that on </p>  <p>Here's how the <code>SearchRequest</code> class is declared (generated by <code>svcutil.exe</code>):</p>  <pre><code>[System.CodeDom.Compiler.GeneratedCodeAttribute("svcutil", "4.6.81.0")] [System.SerializableAttribute()] [System.Diagnostics.DebuggerStepThroughAttribute()] [System.ComponentModel.DesignerCategoryAttribute("code")] [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlTypeAttribute(Namespace="urn:siemens:names:prov:gw:SPML:2:0")] public partial class SearchRequest : SpmlRequest </code></pre>  <p>And the base <code>SpmlRequest</code> class:</p>  <pre><code>[System.Xml.Serialization.XmlIncludeAttribute(typeof(SearchRequest))] [System.CodeDom.Compiler.GeneratedCodeAttribute("svcutil", "4.6.81.0")] [System.SerializableAttribute()] [System.Diagnostics.DebuggerStepThroughAttribute()] [System.ComponentModel.DesignerCategoryAttribute("code")] [System.Xml.Serialization.XmlTypeAttribute(Namespace="urn:siemens:names:prov:gw:SPML:2:0")] public partial class SpmlRequest </code></pre>